To find the desired probability, we integrate over all points $(p,q)$ satisfying $pq(1-p)(1-q) < \frac{\sqrt{3}}{8}$, which corresponds to the shaded region in the figure below.

[asy]
unitsize(3cm);
real f(real p, real q) {
return p*q*(1-p)*(1-q);
}

pair P=(1/2,1/2), Q=(1/2,1/2);

for (real i=0; i<=1; i+=0.1) {
draw((i,0)--(i,1));
}
for (real j=0; j<=1; j+=0.1) {
draw((0,j)--(1,j));
}
fill(P--(0,P.y)--(0,Q.y)--(1,Q.y)--cycle,gray);
draw(circle(P,0.04));
label("A",P,W);
draw((0,0)--(0.2,0.2));
draw((0.2,0.2)--(1-Q.x,1-Q.y));
draw((1-Q.x,1-Q.y)--(1,1));
draw((P.x,0)--(P.x,0.5));
draw((P.x,0.5)--(P.x,1));

label("P",P+E,(1,0));
label("Q",Q+E,(0,1));
[/asy]

